params.commissionParams: commission will be send to author when token's owner sell to someone it. See {NFTStruct-CommissionParams}.

params.amount: amount that need to be paid to owner when some1 buy token
params.consumeToken: erc20 token. if set address(0) then expected coins to pay for NFT

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params.reduceCommissionPercent: commission in percent. can be in interval [0;10000]

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

buy(uint256).notice: buying token. new owner need to pay for nft by coins. Also payment to author is expected

buyWithToken(uint256).notice: buying token. new owner need to pay for nft by tokens(See {NFTStruct-SalesData-erc20Address}). Also payment to author is expected

claimLostToken(address).notice: contract's owner can claim tokens mistekenly sent to this contract

getCommission(uint256).notice: returned commission that will be paid to token's author while transferring NFT

listForSale(uint256,uint256,address).notice: put NFT to list for sale. then anyone can buy it

offerToPayCommission(uint256,uint256).notice: anyone can offer to pay commission to any tokens transfer

reduceCommission(uint256,uint256).notice: reduce commission. author can to allow a token transfer for free to setup reduce commission to 10000(100%)

removeFromSale(uint256).notice: remove NFT from list for sale.

tokensByAuthor(address).notice: can see all the tokens that an author has.
